The holiday is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law defines precisely the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the coming year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Not even in the EU or North America are the holidays unified.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holiday, state holiday and festive days.
The festive days are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical ephemeris.
We celebrate the New Year as well: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven holidays written in red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, commemorating the revolution of 1956.
On August 20 we celebrate the founding of the State, on May 1st the work party, on November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country there are two-day feasts of Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it often becomes a bridge when there is a single working day before or after the party.
In exchange for extended weekends like this, on the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labor that regulates in his specific decree when you have to work exactly in exchange for the day directly before or after the party.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and civil servants.
On the other hand, it is not mandatory for companies and service institutions that, due to their function, work uninterruptedly even during the festive days.
This year the work order can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24 life in the country practically stops, since according to experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
Next year several of our parties will coincide with mid or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working hours than this year.
First the agenda around the work party will be modified so that then, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that in exchange Friday May 2 will be a festive day.
The other change is related to the feast of October 23: on Saturday, October 18, we will have to work instead of Friday, October 24.
On the other hand, the year that comes during the end of the year party will be able to rest, since from December 24 you will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six little deterrents to embitter the lives of your colleagues
Emails that we forget to send, sound messages that we never receive, innocent lies that pass us without realizing it: all of them are part of our “everyday folklore” at work.
You have to decide if you adapt to the small discomforts or consciously avoid confusing situations that can irritate others.
Advice.
Sorry, I forgot to let you know that you’ve been searched by the marketing department,” says one of your colleagues.
That's why you didn't go on a date?
At best he feels it and tries to repair the matter, maybe he calls the marketing department to tell them that he forgot to deliver the message (this is the least usual solution).
In most cases the matter is resolved by apologizing.
Before proceeding to embarrassing explanations, it is worth meditating on the things with which you can embitter the lives of your colleagues and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that is not yours?
There is nothing more irritating than when you want to take a document, an office tool or your phone and you do not find them.
Remember you put the stapler on the table yesterday, but by this morning it disappeared?
Can you find your lost pen on one of your colleagues' desks?
Do not take anything from your colleagues without asking them, because they will rightly be angry with you for stealing their things.
Do not take envelopes or post-it from the office because it can be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out before time.
Do you joke about the private lives of your colleagues?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what are you doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Don’t pass on to everyone the information (guesses) you have about the particular lives of your colleagues!
Don’t abuse your colleague’s trust when he shares his innermost secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, although others also know the things about him.
Are you going on sick leave unjustifiably?
When you call the office on the phone and say that you are sick and your head hurts unbearably, you feel bad or well, you feel that that day you prefer to rest; think that others should do your work, your urgent tasks, your work for term.
Don't screw up your buddy!
If you already know in advance that the next day you will not go to the office or something may happen to you, so you must stay at home, communicate them, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to face your absence the next day.
Tarareos, giggles, phone calls
Are you involved in your work, but are your colleagues’ giggles suddenly taking you out of it?
Have you unwittingly heard a phone conversation that would have been better left unheard?
Do not disturb your colleagues with your hums, songs, conversations out loud (except when you make them above their head), kicks, constant blasphemy, expressing your discontents out loud.
All of these can be annoying, even if you’re not delving into a project right now (writing, planning, organizing).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don’t blame others if you haven’t finished something on time, you’ve forgotten to send an important letter or message!
Don’t allude to the chaos that eventually reigns in the office, or the noise your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that harms others and you must repair the fault!
Ask how you can repair your fault!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and sneakers: very comfortable room for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Don't wear comfortable jogging even if your occupation allows it!
Do not be messy, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday clothes, elegant and beautiful when your occupation demands it!
