The American Federal Reserve Bank, the European Central Bank and the British, Swiss and Canadian Central Banks decided to fight together against the crisis of the Finance Market.
In the Monetary Marking will receive more than one hundred billion dollars through tenders.
In these tenders banks auction the interest rates at which they are able to lend money.
For example, the American Fed will send forty billion dollars to tender, and then another twenty-four billion will be provided by the central banks of Europe and Switzerland.
