What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver for possible accidents, is a significant expense that will depend on several factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to insure or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to insure or the use that is given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for that reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since the statistics reflect that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
Also, drawing on the tallies, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and therefore the probability of having some kind of mishap.
Increasing the frequency increases the odds.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
That is why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 face various disadvantages when it comes to buying insurance at an affordable price, such as the reduced driving experience and the age of the card.
Although the ideal to be well insured is comprehensive insurance, there are other cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk franchise, so that they get the coverages of an all-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would mean that the customer pays a part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim contributed by the client will be preset according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," specifies Luis Noguera, head of Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is assured of protection against damage caused to third parties, although not those caused in their own car.
In addition, you would be covered for theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A tip.
If you are under 25 try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, and may reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base rate.
"Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the company's profit.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase bonuses,” Noguera said.
After 25 years drivers have it easier when taking out insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to hire an all-risk franchise.
“Normally young people can not make use of the experience previously acquired when relying on an accident, and even when driving,” says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates comprehensive insurance, as long as his economic situation allows it, of course.
On the other hand, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with excess (this may be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to afford to assume a greater amount of franchise,” says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, it is recommended a full risk insurance with excess (this being 150 euros), or an extended third party when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver before possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
