According to Warhol, in the exhibition of his works in 1968 at the Moderna Museet Museum hundreds of Shine-cardboard boxes were exhibited. These were not made by Warhol (because of expenses), but were brought directly from the "Shine" cardboard factory.
These were not works of art, but examples (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed the production of wooden Shine-boxes in Sweden, but they were not exhibited at the Modern Museet museum.
Witnesses of those times now speak of that almost fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auction as originals of the "Brillo-Boxes" of "Stockholm type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions some of them were purchased for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden were produced and exposed almost a hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
By this time Warhol had already died for 3 years.
Lars Bystrom, the chief curator of the Moderna Museet museum, investigated six Brillo-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm.
On the contrary, the structure of the copies from the year 1990 shows that the painting was applied with a roller without directly printing the pressed silvers. In addition it is not about oil painting, but acrylic painting.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and should be removed from Andy Warhol’s official Shine-Boxes list,” says Lars Nittve, the director of the Moderna Museet museum and adds that if the “Andy Warhol Art” Authentication Commission in New York will not reach any conclusion, the Moderna Museet museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/exhibition objects.”
As early as July, the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these “grave allegations” involving boxes of soap dust.
But from that moment everything there remained in absolute silence.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
Rebel soldiers who had barricaded themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the downfall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo have surrendered in the Philippines.
Chief Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president for corruption and voter fraud, told a reporter he could not answer for shedding blood.
Soldiers loyal to the government had stormed the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers barricaded themselves in the building a few hours ago.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, had a trial on Thursday for having tried a coup d’état in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, to suddenly be able to deposit with about 30 sympathizers.
Evidently the military police who had to watch him had passed into their ranks and continued their mutiny.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blockaded the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called for an urgent session of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the National Security Advisor, condemned the soldiers’ behavior.
“People are fed up,” Trillanes said.
“We call on people to come into our ranks.”
Gen. Danilo Lim, who previously led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said the other military troops wanted to follow suit soon.
Big government critics called Thursday for a major rally against the president.
His government has been blamed for corruption for months.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986 in the Philippines there have been at least seven attempted coups against the democratically elected government.
United Internet will be Versatel’s largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday the company reported that the average price for a share is 14, 46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the social capital.
There was much speculation about the company’s absorption.
There are also options to increase the financial part in Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made the assumptions about entering the business, after the Brendenberg bank increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market that means that the financial institution holds the participation titles for a third party partner.
United Internet already in the previous day made participate with almost 10 percent to the telecommunications company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the capital increase measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on marketing cooperations for DSL-products.
"We are strengthening our collaboration," the United Internet spokesman said.
The two companies founded a joint venture MSP, to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday United Internet reported that at the start, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, that is, they involve 18.49 percent of Freenet.
That meant both companies kept all options, most notably participation in the Freenet joint stock company.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now, United Internet and Drillisch had a direct 6.01% stake in Freenet.
So they had agreed that Drillisch is going to get the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of the investment company Vatas was already agreed in August.
